    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Towards resolving the problematic status of the digenean genus Astiotrema Looss 1900: Taxa excluded from Astiotrema (sensu stricto) with special reference to plagiorchioid genera closely related to the restricted concept of Astiotrema" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7929521> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7929521>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6–8. Intra-specific variation observed in Ichthyastiotrema fotedari (Dhar, 1977) n. gen., n. comb. 6. I. fotedari (syn. Astiotrema fotedari Dhar, 1977), ventral view, redrawn from Dhar (1977, fig. 1). 7. I. fotedari, ventral view, redrawn from Dhar (1977, fig. 2). 8. I. fotedari (syn. Gauhatiana fusiformis Wang, 1981), dorsal view, redrawn from Wang (1981, fig. 7). Abbreviations:AT, anterior testis; BS, body spines; Ce, cecum; CP, cirrus-pouch; Eg, egg; Es, esophagus; GP, genital pore; Me, metraterm; OS, oral sucker; Ov, ovary; Ph, pharynx; PP, pars prostatica; PT, posterior testis; SV, seminal vesicle; Ut, uterus; VF, vitelline follicle; VS, ventral sucker. Scale bars: Fig. 6 = 500 µm; Fig. 7 = 500 µm; Fig. 8 = 500 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7929521/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

